        <note><p>The <sup>1</sup>H-NMR spectrum of <bold>2b</bold> is interesting in that the resonance at 5.1 ppm appears as a doublet of doublets. The connectivity of the &#x2013;CH(NO<sub>2</sub>)CH<sub>2</sub>CH<sub>3</sub> was verified by a COSY experiment: the dd at &#x3B4; 5.1 correlates with the m at &#x3B4; 2.1, which correlates with the t at &#x3B4; 1.05.  A simple rigid search of the rotation barrier about the C<sup>2</sup>-C<sup>3</sup> bond using CAChe molecular modeling software gave a rotational barrier of 82 kcal/mole. This indicates that the barrier to rotation is large and explains the observed dd at 5.1 ppm for <bold>2b</bold>.</p></note>
